  "prompt": "What is the origin of the word news?",
  "response": "The word \"news\" originated in the 14th century from the Middle English word \"newes,\" which is a plural form of \"new,\" meaning \"new things\" or \"fresh tidings.\" It is believed to have been derived from the Old French word \"noveles,\" which meant \"new things\" or \"news.\" The word \"noveles\" itself came from the Latin \"novella,\" meaning \"new things\" or \"news.\" Over time, the term \"news\" evolved to refer specifically to information about recent events, especially as reported by newspapers, radio, television, or other forms of mass media.",
